divs: Sighting DetailsMy husband and I were watering our garden in our desert home and as it was dark outside, except for the small garden lights, when I decided to take a photo of my husband he held his flashlight under his chin, to make sure so he said I had enough light. He then took one of me. Later when I transferred these digital photos from my camera onto the computer there was this large round greyish blue object in the right hand corner in the sky. I asked my husband what it could be and at first he thought the moon but then changed his mind as he looked closer. We noticed from a prior photo that this same object only much smaller was high in the sky, and then on the one he took of me after I took his the object seemed to be hurtling through space and was getting smaller. I might be wrong but there is no explanation for this object in my photos which I am including below. Sincerely Jean martino
Summary: a large round greyish blue object which looks like it had heiroglyphics on it and a roun rim edge
